        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 5:19PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 518 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pelham, or near Bethel, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Providence...
Milton...
Gatewood...
Blanch...
and Leasburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
north central North Carolina...and south central and west central
Virginia.</instruction>
